  <div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
         <div class="key-point">
          <h3>How do we get paid?</h3>
          <p>
             We commonly get asked by our clients how we get paid if we don't charge a fee? 
          </p>

          <p>
            The majority of mortgage brokers charge a fee anywhere from £200 - £500 for a mortgage application, on top of the fee that they charge you they will also be paid a fee by the Bank or Building Society that you are applying to, this is called a procuration fee.
          </p>
          <p>
            Every mortgage product on the market has a procuration fee built into it, if you go directly to the Bank the procuration fee will still be included but this portion of the deal will be used to pay the salary of the Banks in house mortgage adviser, if you apply through a Broker the fee will instead be paid to the brokers firm.
          </p>
          <p>
            At Mortgages Northern Ireland we don't beleive in charging fees, we believe that if we have a streamlined fast efficient system in place the procuration fee paid from the Bank is more than enough for us to remain profitable. 
          </p>
          <p>
            The product that you apply for with Mortgages Northern Ireland will in 99% of occasions be exactly the same product that you would get directly from the Bank and in some cases we have access to exclusive deals that you would not get if you walked into the Bank from the High Street.
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

